sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant HW as Timer Hardware
    participant CPU as ARM Core
    participant IRQ_ASM as exception_entry_irq
    participant IRQ_C as timer_isr
    participant SCHED as scheduler_tick
    participant TASK as Current Task
    participant CS as context_switch
    
    %% --- HARDWARE PHASE ---
    Note over HW,CPU: 1. INTERRUPT TRIGGER
    HW->>CPU: Assert IRQ Line
    CPU->>IRQ_ASM: Jump to Vector (IRQ Mode)
    
    %% --- IRQ HANDLING PHASE ---
    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
    Note over IRQ_ASM: 2. IRQ ENTRY
    IRQ_ASM->>IRQ_C: timer_isr()
    
    IRQ_C->>SCHED: scheduler_tick()
    Note right of SCHED: Set need_reschedule = true
    SCHED-->>IRQ_C: return
    
    IRQ_C->>IRQ_ASM: return
    Note right of IRQ_ASM: Restore Context<br/>Perform EOI
    end
    
    IRQ_ASM-->>TASK: Exception Return (SVC Mode)
    
    %% --- COOPERATIVE YIELD PHASE ---
    rect rgb(255, 250, 240)
    Note over TASK: 3. TASK EXECUTION
    Note right of TASK: Task Loop checks<br/>need_reschedule flag
    
    TASK->>CS: scheduler_yield() called
    Note right of CS: Called in SVC Mode<br/>(Normal Function Call)
    end
    
    %% --- CONTEXT SWITCH PHASE ---
    rect rgb(255, 235, 235)
    Note over CS: 4. CONTEXT SWITCH (SVC)
    
    Note right of CS: SAVE CONTEXT:<br/>Push {r4-r11, LR}<br/>(Callee-saved only)
    
    Note right of CS: LOAD CONTEXT:<br/>SP = next->sp<br/>Pop {r4-r11, LR}
    end
    
    CS-->>TASK: Return to Next Task
    Note right of TASK: Resumes execution